c83fe570ba6a090","tid":1639011,"uid":134071,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T13:22:35.000Z","msg":"十月最新民調: 華倫險勝拜登<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://hannity.com/media-room/bad-news-for-biden-elizabeth-warren-takes-the-top-spot-in-new-national-poll/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhannity.com%2Fmedia-room%2Fbad-news-for-biden-elizabeth-warren-takes-the-top-spot-in-new-national-poll%2F&d=cH2nQL%2B7gNVGRZzFZPB6VkBBI%2BG%2BtQAW9Loz3QxUp%2BM%3D&h=2121da67\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://hannity.com/media-room/bad-news-for-biden-elizabeth-warren-takes-the-top-spot-in-new-national-poll/</a><br />\n<br />\nBad News for Biden: Elizabeth Warren Takes the Top Spot in New National Poll<br />\nposted by Hannity Staff - 17 hours ago<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Senator Elizabeth Warren overtook former Vice President Joe Biden in another national poll this week; </strong>solidifying her position as a potential frontrunner for the Democratic nomination.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Elizabeth Warren has taken a narrow lead over Joe Biden in the race for the Democratic presidential nomination, the October IBD/TIPP Poll found. Both candidates continue to lead in a head-to-head matchup against President Trump, though Biden had a more comfortable lead, outside the margin of error,&rdquo; reports the survey.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;<strong>Elizabeth Warren had the support of 27%, with Joe Biden backed by 26%</strong> and Bernie Sanders a distant third at 10%. Support for South Bend, Ind., Mayor Pete Buttigieg climbed to 7% from 5%. No other candidate polled more than 3%,&rdquo; adds the report.<br />\n<br />\nThe poll comes days after Warren&rsquo;s campaign &ldquo;blew past&rdquo; Biden in 3rd quarter fundraising; a major indicator of voter enthusiasm heading into the primary season.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The figure affirms the momentum Warren has appeared to be gaining in recent weeks and months, as polls show her now battling Biden &ndash; once the unrivaled front-runner &ndash; for the primary lead,&rdquo; reports Fox News.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I&rsquo;m grateful down to my toes for every grassroots supporter who chipped in to help raise $24.6 million in the third fundraising quarter. Together, we&rsquo;re building a movement that&rsquo;s going to put power back in the hands of the people,&rdquo; posted Warren on social media."},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T13:37:41.000Z","msg":"而家拜登畀侵打成賣國賊"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T14:20:57.000Z","msg":"咁佢真係<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a364b82dc15e05a5baaed8f94e6b5e56157f9842","tid":1639011,"uid":134071,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"32c6337e464e99011dde7e269cc2dee0b95a4476","tid":1639011,"uid":64962,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T14:19:47.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T14:21:11.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"215aca2b0dfe51db0347a223676883f83dd31313","tid":1639011,"uid":74272,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"c53aa0be695210fc2cc396b21079c9a297157f41","tid":1639011,"uid":284100,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"774cffc35fdf9a434c058ec8733dab32fc332735","tid":1639011,"uid":217270,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T13:43:14.000Z","msg":"其實對香港黎講，係咪得拜登做總統先係壞結果？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T13:45:24.000Z","msg":"我覺得喺"},"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T14:23:11.000Z","msg":"仲有一個姓楊既候選人<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"788cf16b9918c64504cb9bb6f844e58a79aef7ee","tid":1639011,"uid":284100,"like":3,"dislike":0,"scor